Yeah, I don't see her either.

273
00:15:29,320 --> 00:15:33,440
Gor, we're
fighting them, right?

274
00:15:33,440 --> 00:15:35,240
Myath.

275
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:36,640
Uh, oh, aaah!

276
00:15:36,640 --> 00:15:41,000
[THUD]

277
00:15:42,400 --> 00:15:43,520
‐ Want to look?
‐ Hm?

278
00:15:43,520 --> 00:15:44,320
Thanks.

279
00:15:50,880 --> 00:15:53,040
That bus is headed here.

280
00:16:00,040 --> 00:16:01,480
WOMAN (ON INTERCOM):
Attention, passengers.

281
00:16:01,480 --> 00:16:04,240
The bus has left Myath and is
currently traveling at a speed

282
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:07,640
of 50 kilmels per hour.

283
00:16:07,640 --> 00:16:09,720
We're en route to our
next scheduled stop, which

284
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:13,080
is the academic of Zuellni.

285
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:14,680
Scans show that our
path to Zuellni‐‐

286
00:16:14,680 --> 00:16:16,600
Looks like we're finally
going to get there.

287
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:19,040
Yeah, it didn't take half
as long as I thought it would.

288
00:16:19,040 --> 00:16:21,000
WOMAN (ON INTERCOM): So please
sit back and enjoy the ride

289
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:22,000
It's just right over there.

290
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:22,760
You see?

291
00:16:22,760 --> 00:16:25,280
It's in the same direction
as the setting sun.

292
00:16:25,280 --> 00:16:28,680
That's it, huh?

293
00:16:28,680 --> 00:16:30,240
That's Zuellni.

294
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:32,400
I'm here, where Layfon is.

295
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:36,640
LEERIN'S FATHER (VOICEOVER):
I'd like you to deliver

296
00:16:36,640 --> 00:16:38,040
this to Layfon for me.

297
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:40,560
Huh?

298
00:16:40,560 --> 00:16:41,640
I've prepared it for him.

299
00:16:41,640 --> 00:16:44,120
If he asks, tell him that
it's a reward for learning all

300
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:46,720
of the Saiharden techniques.

301
00:16:46,720 --> 00:16:48,720
I'm to give this to Layfon?

302
00:17:00,880 --> 00:17:04,680
We've already set up command
HQ in the student council room.

303
00:17:04,680 --> 00:17:06,240
We're also beginning
startup prep

304
00:17:06,240 --> 00:17:08,520
of the municipal defense
system and a final check

305
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:10,280
of all the shelters too.

306
00:17:10,280 --> 00:17:12,800
Will this really be
a municipal battle?

307
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:15,240
Yes, there can be
little doubt about that.

308
00:17:15,240 --> 00:17:16,640
Therefore, all
platoon members are

309
00:17:16,640 --> 00:17:18,480
to stand by in the
military training

310
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:20,120
hall until otherwise ordered.

311
00:17:20,120 --> 00:17:21,200
Dismissed.

312
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:22,000
ALL: Sir.

313
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:23,880
MAN (ON INTERCOM): All
platoon members on standby,

314
00:17:23,880 --> 00:17:26,120
please proceed to your
individual waiting rooms

315
00:17:26,120 --> 00:17:27,560
and refrain from undue egress.

316
00:17:27,560 --> 00:17:30,120
I repeat, all platoon members‐‐

317
00:17:30,120 --> 00:17:31,360
PLATOON MEMBER 1:
There's a problem

318
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:32,800
with the flash headers in the
Sixth Platoon waiting room.

319
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:33,600
Fix them.

320
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:34,800
PLATOON MEMBER 2: Portable med
distribution is running late.

321
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:37,000
PLATOON MEMBER 3: Rescue squads
are to assemble at command HQ.

322
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:37,920
I'm on my way.

323
00:17:37,920 --> 00:17:38,920
See you there.

324
00:17:58,560 --> 00:18:05,720
This is‐‐ (ANGRILY) Argh!

325
00:18:15,040 --> 00:18:17,240
Things just get
more interesting.

326
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:21,920
Kidnapped?

327
00:18:21,920 --> 00:18:27,320
Yes, by the Salinban Mercenary
Group, by Haia, to be exact.

328
00:18:27,320 --> 00:18:29,320
But what for?

329
00:18:29,320 --> 00:18:32,480
Because Haia wants to force
Layfon into a one‐on‐one fight.

330
00:18:32,480 --> 00:18:35,560
He says to come alone tomorrow
to a place that he'll name.

331
00:18:35,560 --> 00:18:37,600
Where's the
mercenaries' roaming bus?

332
00:18:37,600 --> 00:18:40,280
It's not at our designated
lodging facilities.

333
00:18:40,280 --> 00:18:41,640
I'm assuming they're
hiding somewhere

334
00:18:41,640 --> 00:18:43,560
beyond our outer border.

335
00:18:43,560 --> 00:18:46,000
Of all the times.

336
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:48,240
Mr. President,
I'd like to humbly

337
00:18:48,240 --> 00:18:52,480
ask your permission to allow
Layfon to rescue Felli.

338
00:18:52,480 --> 00:18:55,080
It can't be helped.

339
00:18:55,080 --> 00:18:58,000
Myath is approaching and
will reach Zuellni soon.

340
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:00,200
What do you plan to do if
the municipal battle begins

341
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:01,640
before the rescue is complete?

342
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:02,920
Kalian.

343
00:19:02,920 --> 00:19:04,800
Don't worry about us.

344
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:07,400
We'll find a way to make
up for their absence.

345
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:08,760
I don't think
a platoon without

346
00:19:08,760 --> 00:19:11,480
its Nen‐I operator would be
able to perform all that well.

347
00:19:11,480 --> 00:19:12,280
Do you?

348
00:19:12,280 --> 00:19:14,640
Even so, we will, sir.

349
00:19:14,640 --> 00:19:16,120
But how, Captain?

350
00:19:16,120 --> 00:19:19,520
Are you saying that you
have some concrete strategy?

351
00:19:19,520 --> 00:19:21,320
No No, sir.

352
00:19:21,320 --> 00:19:23,120
Kalian.

353
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:26,560
Sir, I can do it.

354
00:19:26,560 --> 00:19:28,760
I'm going to save Felli.

355
00:19:28,760 --> 00:19:30,120
Zuellni too.

356
00:19:33,040 --> 00:19:35,000
Layfon.

357
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:39,400
[MUSIC PLAYING]

358
00:19:43,320 --> 00:19:44,320
Excuse me.

359
00:19:50,680 --> 00:19:54,160
Vanze, I need you to
rethink our combat strategies.

360
00:19:54,160 --> 00:19:58,680
Zuellni must be victorious
without Layfon's participation.

361
00:19:58,680 --> 00:19:59,480
Thank you, sir.

362
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:04,600
It was common sense.

363
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:09,560
Layfon Alseif can't be
stopped by me or anyone else.

364
00:20:30,480 --> 00:20:35,480
[SIREN WAILS]

365
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:52,000
So this is it, Zuellni.

366
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:54,800
And Layfon is somewhere out
there in the city right now.

367
00:20:58,240 --> 00:20:59,480
Well, here's your luggage.

368
00:20:59,480 --> 00:21:00,560
Oh, thank you.

369
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:02,320
It's been really
interesting, Leerin.

370
00:21:02,320 --> 00:21:03,240
See ya.

371
00:21:03,240 --> 00:21:05,640
Thank you so much
for watching over me.

372
00:21:05,640 --> 00:21:06,560
Ah, it's OK.

373
00:21:06,560 --> 00:21:08,480
All I did was fulfill a promise.

374
00:21:08,480 --> 00:21:10,200
Senola will be happy at least.

375
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:11,000
Huh?

376
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:11,760
Senola?

377
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:16,680
I rate your chest
10 million points.

378
00:21:20,760 --> 00:21:21,600
Wait.

379
00:21:21,600 --> 00:21:23,520
Are you saying
Senola was the one

380
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:24,720
who asked you to look after me?

381
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:26,200
Did I hear you correctly?

382
00:21:26,200 --> 00:21:29,160
But why would she do that?

383
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:30,000
Hey, listen.

384
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:32,400
I'm sorry, but I'm in
a bit of a hurry here.

385
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:35,360
You'll learn the answer to
that question soon enough.

386
00:21:35,360 --> 00:21:37,640
[GASP] Savaris, no, wait!

387
00:21:40,480 --> 00:21:42,480
It's sunrise.

388
00:21:42,480 --> 00:21:44,600
It's almost time, guys.

389
00:21:44,600 --> 00:21:49,080
[MUSIC PLAYING]

390
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:17,760
Things sure have
gotten complicated.

391
00:22:17,760 --> 00:22:23,240
[MUSIC PLAYING]

392
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:36,480
[SINGING IN JAPANESE]

393
00:24:00,560 --> 00:24:02,120
NARRATOR: Felli has
been taken hostage,

394
00:24:02,120 --> 00:24:04,520
and Layfon has a
one‐on‐one duel with Haia.

395
00:24:04,520 --> 00:24:06,880
But Haia is of the same
Saiharden fighting style

396
00:24:06,880 --> 00:24:08,600
and uses its single‐edged
sword, giving

397
00:24:08,600 --> 00:24:10,480
Layfon a far greater challenge.

398
00:24:10,480 --> 00:24:14,840
Next time, Felli
kidnapped and restoration.

